definitions.definition: ( numismatics , historical ) The gold-backed monetary unit of Latvia from August 1922 until April 1941, when it was replaced by the Soviet ruble ; it was typically pegged at about 25 to the British pound .
( numismatics , historical ) The floating fiat monetary unit of Latvia from 1992 until January 2014, when it was replaced by the euro .
A coin or bill of either currency .
